(1)
First Ave., east side, north from East 49th Street and Mitchell Place to 50th (Dunscomb Place) Streets. Also shown is Mitchell Place, at, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner of First Ave. These buildings will be demolished, to make way for the Beekman Towers.

September 20, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same after demolition.
October 29, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

First Avenue, west side, from East 49th to 50th Streets. The corner row in the center is to be demolished. Views 2 and 3 show this site at various dates. The dominant skyscraper in the background, is the Ritz Tower, an apartment hotel at Park Avenue and
57th Street.
View 1:  October 24, 1928
View 2:  July 3, 1934
View 3:  July 23, 1939
P. L. Sperr
